<div class="col-lg-6 col-md-12"><br>
    <h3 class="text-left">How We Use the Data</h3><br>

    This operational data is used across government agencies to extend and further improve upon their work. These
    support projects like,<br><br>
    <li>Transportation Planning with<a href="http://opendata.dc.gov/datasets/street-centerlines"> Street and Road</a>
        networks
    </li>
    <li><a href="https://www.dcwater.com/impervious-area-charge">Raising Revenue</a> as a result of<a
        href="http://opendata.dc.gov/datasets?q=impervious%20surface%202015"> Impervious Surfaces</a></li>
    <li><a
        href="http://dcgis.maps.arcgis.com/apps/SimpleMapViewer/index.html?appid=9565681ce5c14eba8275949f5e30d747&webmap=40e1d45c20c8437091f34af1d47c6418">Urban
        Landscape Planning</a> with<a href="http://opendata.dc.gov/datasets/existing-land-use"> Existing</a> and<a
        href="http://opendata.dc.gov/datasets/future-land-use"> Future</a> Land Use
    </li>
</div>
